{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:37:54.314906+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 28870c502f5a167ed7b32ca30547a3f3b327a567)", "id": "lc_853d1ccf-54a7-425c-8268-c13493e01bbe"}, {"type": "text", "text": "thresholds:\n  high: fail\n  medium: warn\n  low: pass\n", "id": "lc_90a34e97-792d-4836-bab1-63aeb5e2321e"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "8399fd36-1995-439b-aee9-d0dd6582c23f", "tool_call_id": "call_968c5f2900b74ef78bb8c42f", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:37:54.329316+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 0d83409601cf31954d0ddfd0b4f622aea70dd570)", "id": "lc_e6095983-76df-427b-98e7-59c295a72003"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# ZAP Findings Policy Toolkit\n\nA policy and reporting repository for triaging ZAP alerts, maintaining endpoint scope, and documenting baseline scan decisions.\n\n## Project layout\n\n- `policy/` — Risk handling and endpoint allowlist configuration.\n- `sample_data/` — Representative ZAP alert fixtures.\n- `reports/` — Generated triage summaries.\n- `docs/` — Policy and scope documentation.\n- `scripts/` — Report summarization helpers.\n\n## Quick start\n\n```bash\nmake validate\n```\n```bash\npython3 scripts/summarize_zap_alerts.py\n```\n\n## Baseline review workflow\n\n1. Run or inspect the local demo application.\n2. Review ZAP policy files before changing alert handling.\n3. Convert JSON outputs into Markdown summaries for review.\n4. Keep endpoint scope documentation current.\n\nThe scan helper is scoped to local demo targets.\n\n## Maintenance notes\n\nPolicy files describe local demo endpoints and baseline triage behavior.\n\n## Contributing\n\nKeep changes focused, update documentation when behavior changes, and run the validation commands before submitting a pull request.\n", "id": "lc_1aaeed7a-a78c-4eb8-8998-5fa24002e866"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "0b0a4f98-d445-4b56-a563-d5513e3e7893", "tool_call_id": "call_d34a58da6b7944c29a4078f4", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:37:54.329544+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 44d7c5b3c3a345a02f3debec6c52ca6bd2c001ac)", "id": "lc_abc7f7c6-323c-4b0b-8fa1-c03ffd02d65d"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# OWASP ZAP baseline configuration for local demo app\n# Format: rule_id   action   reason\n10020\tWARN\tMissing anti-clickjacking header is accepted for this local text-only demo.\n", "id": "lc_d95a1a24-0079-4e11-97c6-9118d0859bf7"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "4555ec94-097e-4eae-a186-b26a74457be0", "tool_call_id": "call_43db9be8b83c4c768f18bed5", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:37:54.338823+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: c755ca511a4a430d89dbab3848ccdbad1ceab7ca)", "id": "lc_6102dd04-474f-4b38-81b4-b699e873e022"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport sys\n\nroot = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\nrequired = ['README.md', 'SECURITY.md', 'zap/baseline.conf', 'sample_data/zap_baseline.json', 'scripts/run_zap_baseline.sh']\nerrors = []\nfor rel in required:\n    if not (root / rel).exists():\n        errors.append(f'missing required file: {rel}')\n\n\nrunner = (root / 'scripts' / 'run_zap_baseline.sh').read_text()\nif 'Refusing non-local target' not in runner:\n    errors.append('scripts/run_zap_baseline.sh must reject non-local targets')\n\nif errors:\n    for error in errors:\n        print(error, file=sys.stderr)\n    sys.exit(1)\nprint('OK: T14_R02')\n", "id": "lc_f791f334-5992-420a-bda1-2aeea57b331e"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "d483c9d2-ddba-4f24-9b61-b754adbba423", "tool_call_id": "call_a2ada02f539c4cbd8742c3c8", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
